On 2025-07-20, I could not get `cargo install c2rust` to work.

Here is what I did instead:

## Ensure there is only one version of LLVM and clang installed:
# Remove all numbered versions of clang and llvm; obtain them by running dpkg -l:
dpkg -l | grep 'clang|llvm'
# DO NOT remove: libllvm19 libllvm20

sudo apt update
sudo apt remove -y \
  clang \
  llvm \
  llvm-dev \
  llvm-runtime:amd64 \
  || true
for ver in 14 15 16 17 18 19 20; do
  sudo apt remove -y \
    clang-${ver} clang-tools-${ver} clangd-${ver} lld-${ver} \
    libclang-common-${ver}-dev libclang-common-${ver}-dev:amd64 libclang-cpp${ver} \
    llvm-${ver} llvm-${ver}-dev llvm-${ver}-linker-tools llvm-${ver}-runtime llvm-${ver}-tools \
    || true
done
sudo apt install -y clang llvm llvm-dev


# Install unnumbered versions, which will all be consistent with one another:
sudo apt install -y clang libclang-dev llvm llvm-dev

cargo install --git https://github.com/immunant/c2rust.git c2rust
